text: "There's been more damage than anyone expected, and these mayors, I think, are doing a phenomenal job of making sure the people in their communities are safe," said Gottheimer. https://t.co/iIOnWcBPSu
Let’s pray that everyone stays safe and warm in the coming days and offer our deepest sympathies to the Andover family who lost a loved one to the storm this weekend.

I’m determined to do everything I can, coordinating with state and local officials, to help facilitate a speedy recovery and make sure that utility companies are prioritizing customer needs and safety first and foremost.
If you’ve had trouble contacting emergency services at your utility company or if you have any other issues, please let me know by contacting my office at https://t.co/Y2fCcy9lH7 or 973-940-1117.

If your power is STILL OUT, please make sure to first contact your utility company. Knowing where the worst problems are will help. 
Jersey Central Power and Light: 888-544-4877 
Sussex Rural Electric Cooperative: 877-504-6463
You can find nearby warming stations by calling 2-1-1 or going to https://t.co/c5yFqXUzeK.
Whether it’s  volunteering at a warming center or providing free meals for the hungry, our Jersey values are shining brightly even during this dark disaster.
Thank you to the many residents and businesses that have gone the extra mile to care for your neighbors and for being extra careful with the live wires.

I’ve also spoken the power companies to press then for clear timelines and answers. I will keep working with your excellent mayors in pushing them until every last light is on and every last tree is cleared.

I’ve been working closely with everyone from mayors and DPWs to our state representatives and the Governor to make sure that recovery efforts are as speedy as possible. Our phenomenal first responders have gone the extra mile, as always.

No one in Northwest Jersey has been spared by this brutal storm. Many estimates expect some residents in Sussex & Warren to go two more days without power. I share the deep frustration many have expressed in the turn-around, especially as we face another storm arriving Wednesday.

I want actual tax cuts for New Jersey, and I’ve been working across the aisle to get tax cuts. But this Tax Hike Bill represents yet another huge giveaway to Moocher States like Mississippi and Alabama — at the cost of a huge tax hike on our backs.
It’s another nail in New Jersey’s coffin.

It eliminates our ability to deduct state and local income taxes, brings back the AMT, and nearly eliminates our ability to deduct our property taxes and mortgage interest.   It will send jobs, people and businesses fleeing from our state and send housing prices plummeting.
That’s why everyone--from the New Jersey Chamber of Commerce to law enforcement to nearly every member of the Congressional delegation, Democrat and Republican alike--voted against the Tax Hike Bill.

This Tax Hike Bill is unmitigated assault and tax hike on New Jersey families and businesses. And, what’s worse, by eliminating the deductions we rely on, it’s a broken promise to every resident and business in our state.
